
.pd2y
  h2 Features
  hr
  .pd1y
    p → Works as a terminal/file manager or ssh/sftp/ftp/telnet/serialport/RDP/VNC client
    p → Support Window 7+(X64/ARM64), Mac OS 10.15+(x64/arm64), Linux(x64/arm64), even old Linux with glibc 2.17+ like UOS/Kylin/Ubuntu 18.04 etc
    p → Global hotkey to toggle window visibility (similar to guake, default is ctrl + 2)
    p → Multi platform(linux, mac, win)
    p → 🇺🇸 🇨🇳 🇧🇷 🇷🇺 🇪🇸 🇫🇷 🇹🇷 🇭🇰 🇯🇵 🇸🇦 🇩🇪 🇰🇷 🇮🇩 🇵🇱 Multi-language support(#[a(href='https://github.com/electerm/electerm-locales', rel='noreferrer', target='_blank') electerm-locales], contributions/fixes welcome)
    p → Double click to directly edit (small) remote files.
    p → Auth with publicKey + password.
    p → Support Zmodem(rz, sz).
    p → Support ssh tunnel.
    p → Support #[a(href='https://github.com/trzsz/trzsz', rel='noreferrer', target='_blank') Trzsz](trz/tsz), similar to rz/sz, and compatible with tmux.
    p → Transparent window(Mac, win).
    p → Terminal background image.
    p → Global/session proxy.
    p → Quick commands
    p → UI/terminal theme
    p → Sync bookmarks/themes/quick commands to github/gitee secret gist
    p → Quick input to one or all terminals.
    p → AI assistant integration (supporting #[a(href='https://www.deepseek.com', rel='noreferrer', target='_blank') DeepSeek], OpenAI, and other AI APIs) to help with command suggestions, script writing, and explaining selected terminal content
    p → Deep link support: Open connections with URLs like telnet://192.168.2.31:34554 or ssh://user@host:22 - see #[a(href='https://github.com/electerm/electerm/wiki/Deep-link-support', rel='noreferrer', target='_blank') Deep link support wiki]
    p
      span → Command line usage: check
      a.mg1l(href='https://github.com/electerm/electerm/wiki/Command-line-usage', rel='noreferrer', target='_blank') wiki

.pd2y
  h2 Links
  hr
  .pd1y
    each val, i in links
      p
        // Show main link
        a(href=val.url, rel='noreferrer', target='_blank', title=val.title)
          if val.image
            img(src=val.image, alt=val.title)
          else
            span ✴ #{val.title}
        // Show special CN link if present, with clear separation
        if val.urlCn && val.titleCn
          span
            a.mg1l(href=val.urlCn, rel='noreferrer', target='_blank', title=val.titleCn)
              span / #{val.titleCn}

.pd2y
  h2 Star History
  hr
  .pd1y.aligncenter
    a(href='https://www.star-history.com/#electerm/electerm&Date', rel='noreferrer', target='_blank', title='Star History Chart')
      img(src='https://api.star-history.com/svg?repos=electerm/electerm&type=Date', alt='Star History Chart')
